CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 5, 1946, pg. 10 reads: "Newlyweds - Miss Mary Alice Wilson of Beltzhoover became the bride of James Matthews on Sept. 10 in an attractive ceremony held at the home of her aunt, Mrs. Naomi Mosley. The Rev. I .Jones of Beulah Baptist Church, officiated.  A reception was held immediately following the ceremony.  The newlyweds will live in Pittsburgh. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of bride Mary Alice Wilson Matthews and groom James Matthews cutting three tiered cake in home of Naomi Mosley
